cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.PL, cs.CR, cs.FL

The paper discusses models of computation and their expressiveness, which suggests it belongs to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. The paper specifically focuses on interactive and reactive Turing machines, which are related to Information Theory (cs.IT) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the computability of stream translations, which is related to Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the expressiveness of reactive Turing machines with advice, which is related to Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category.
